boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Portland Center for the Performing Arts Business Office: 503-248-4335 Weather Related Info: 503-274-6592 TDD: 503-796-9342 (box office) 503-796-0122 (business office)
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Arlene Schnitzer box office opens 2 hours prior to the performance. Advance tickets are available through www.ticketmaster.com, Charge-By-Phone (503)224-4400 or at local Ticketmaster outlets.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: The Arlene Schnitzer box office accepts cash and check (with check guarantee card). Visa and Mastercard are also accepted for most events.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call opens 2 hours prior to the performance.

venues.parkingDetail: Pay parking is available on 6th St. Other lots within a 2 block radius. There is a parking structure in the Broadway Building across the street and surface lots on SW 10th and Main. Public: 3 blocks from the Pioneer Square MAX stop. Rules/Regulations: Most touring shows do not allow reentry if someone leaves the building.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: The wheelchair/accessible seats are on the outside aisle of sections A and D on the main floor and row HH in the same sections. It is always seat 1 in section A and the higher numbered seat in section D on the outside aisle. These are theatre seats and must be unbolted and removed for a wheelchair. Accessible aisle seat is the even X-number, the companion is the odd X-number. If you are selling into an account, please indicate in the Extra line to keep or remove the seat. Row HH is 6 moveable, padded chairs and a wheelchair can sit anywhere along the row.

generalInfo.generalRule: No flash cameras allowed inside No recording devices No smoking inside building Late comers must wait in lobby to be seated by an usher during a convenient pause in the performance.

venues.name: Edgefield

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Box Office and Doors open 1 1/2 hours prior to showtime. Showtime's vary by event.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Located in front of the Main Entrance on the Southwest end of the amphitheater, near the front entrance to the Edgefield Hotel.

venues.parkingDetail: Free Parking in the East and West grass lots located south off of Halsey St. Parking directly in front of Edgefield is reserved for hotel guests and individuals with disabilities only.

generalInfo.generalRule: All events are held rain or shine. All sales are FINAL. NO REFUNDS. Re-entry to the venue will not be allowed for events unless otherwise noted. Any person under the age of 21 found drinking on the premises will be evicted without refund. Smoking will be allowed in designated areas only. No camping, RV's or camping trailers. No tailgating. No moshing or crowd surfing. All guests and their personal possessions are subject to inspection prior to venue admittance. PERMITTED ITEMS AT ALL EVENTS (unless otherwise noted): Binoculars Blankest & Beach Towels Disposable Cameras Sealed Bottled Water Low Profile Lawn Chairs NON-PERMITTED ITEMS FOR ALL EVENTS: Fireworks Play Pens Throwing Toys (including Beach Balls & frisbees) Laser Pointers High Profile Lawn Chairs Coolers, Baskets or Large Bags Outside food or beverages (SEALED Bottled Water is OK) Cameras or Recording Devices of any kind Weapons Drugs Musical Instruments or Drums Animals (except for service animals) Skateboards, Scooters or Skates of any kind Large (golf) Umbrellas or Flags
generalInfo.childRule: Accompanied children ages 2 and younger and welcome in to the venue at no charge.

venues.name: Les Schwab Amphitheater

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Box Office and Gates open 1 1/2 hours prior to showtime. Varies by event.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Located in front of Main Entrance on the southwest side of the venue.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is free in the Old Mill District and the Mt. Bachelor park & ride lots. Handicapped Parking: Drop off is available at the Box Office. Parking only available in the Old Mill District.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: For Wheelchair accessible seating, purchase general admission tickets. There is a designated area at stage right, for wheelchair patrons and one companion.

generalInfo.generalRule: No re-entry, everyone will be subject to search upon entry. No high back chairs or elevated seats allowed. No smoking except in the designated venue areas. No stage diving or crowd surfing. No professional cameras (video or still), recording devices, alcoholic beverages, cans or bottles, fireworks, outside food or beverage, skateboards, frisbees, pets, picnic baskets, cooler ice chests, weapons, guns, knives, chains, explosives, laser pointers, unbreallas, instruments, tents, flags, bota bags, backpacks or large bags. If you are in doubt don't bring it.
generalInfo.childRule: Children, 24 months and under are admitted free in the general admission lawn area. No one is free in the Golden Circle reserved seating areas. ALL AGES ARE WELCOME.

ada.adaPhones: For additional information about Accessible Seating please call the Les Schwab Amphitheater at 541-322-9383.
ada.adaCustomCopy: To accommodate accessible seating patrons, Les Schwab Amphitheater allows wheelchair patrons and one companion to sit in a special reserved section at the Amphitheater.  Wheelchair accessible patrons purchase a general admission ticket (even for shows with Golden Circle seating) and then when they arrive at the amphitheater they are directed to the seating area.  In order to accommodate all of the wheelchair patrons, only one companion seat is allowed per wheelchair.  Additional members of your party should sit in the general seating area.  If you have additional questions please contact the venue directly at 541-322-9383.
ada.adaHours: Box Office and Gates generally open 1 1/2 prior to showtime. This schedule may vary by event.
